                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d207">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.114/174</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-13T15:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 13, 1918, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1347. Your 1616, September 4, 5 p.m. Substance telegraphed to Peking. Legation
                    has also been advised that the information which the Department has received
                    makes it plain that the plan in contemplation, for the disposition of opium
                    stocks is in contravention of the spirit of the Hague draft treaty ratified by
                    the United States and China and jeopardizes all the beneficial results that have
                    been accomplished, at so much sacrifice, towards the suppression of the opium
                    traffic. Legation will make representations to the Chinese Government in the
                    above sense and has been instructed to cooperate as closely as possible with the
                    British Minister. You will so inform Foreign Office and express the hope that
                    British Minister at Peking will be instructed to make similar
                    representations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
